[[File:Gate of Uprightness.JPG|thumb|right|The gate in 2008]]
'''Duanmen''', also known as the '''Gate of Uprightness''', or '''Upright Gate''', is a gate in [[Beijing]]'s [[Imperial City, Beijing|Imperial City]], and is located south of the [[Forbidden City]]. Proceeding north from the entrance to the Imperial City, it is the next gate after the [[Tian'anmen]], or Gate of Heavenly Peace, and has a similar structure to that gate. The next gate further north is the [[Meridian Gate]], which is the southern and main gate to the Forbidden City itself.<ref name="Global">{{cite book|title=A Global History of Architecture|date=October 4, 2011|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|page=1140|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HL2I_t_ZyQoC&pg=PT1140&lpg=PT1140&dq#v=onepage&q&f=false|accessdate=19 November 2017|first1=Mark M.|last1=Jarzombek|first2=Vikramaditya|last2=Prakash}}</ref>

